 newBuilder(plugin).name and checking if Metadata can be copied the same way. It's a bit similar but not identical, and I wonder if we can keep both options available?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering serialization behavior**\\n\\nI'm thinking about public classes and whether they have a Serializable marker but aren't really serializing. If that's the case, it could mean direct serialization is prohibited. But then again, I wonder if I can test the `SnapshotVersion` value for equality? It seems like I can, but can I only test that `SnapshotVersion` has equality while others might just be identity? That doesn’t seem to be a feature I can rely on.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a new test in:\n\n`tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-api-metadata/4.0.0-rc-5/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_api_metadata/Maven_api_metadataTest.java`\n\nWhat I added:\n- Analyzed existing coverage: current tests already cover full model construction, defaults, builder collection immutability, direct `with*` copy behavior, builders from existing instances, and `SnapshotVersion` equality.\n- Added coverage for a distinct feature not directly tested before: collection-valued `with*` methods defensively copy mutable inputs and expose immutable lists.\n  - `Metadata.withPlugins(...)`\n  - `Versioning.withVersions(...)`\n  - `Versioning.withSnapshotVersions(...)`\n\nThe new test verifies:\n- Original instances remain unchanged.\n- Mutable input collections are defensively copied.\n- Returned collections remain immutable.\n\nI did not modify build files or existing test logic. I did not run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01ca6cb4bf2610340169fdf3f6faf8819f9e0bfe70e0c2878b\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 868, "output": 1417, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35053, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "t